truth: Mark.
mark: Hey. 
truth: I need anything useful you've got. 
mark: What counts as "useful" to you? 
truth: Stuff you noticed that we didn't. A new perspective. 
truth: [color=#e85670][i] Why does that sound so vague? Get it together. [/i]
mark: New perspective... getting all philosophical now, huh? "Beauty is in the eye of the beholder" type shit. 
truth: How does that have anything to do with this? Come on, man. This is serious. 
truth: [color=#e85670][i] Mark scratches his head, brow furrowing. He looks like he’s digging for something. [/i]
mark: I mean... there was one thing. 
mark: When we got to the hobby store, me and Kevin usually hit the tabletop section. Same as always. 
mark: But this time? He went straight to the opposite end. 
truth: Ok... and?
mark: I called after him, but he just said something about “expanding his horizons” or whatever. 
truth: Hmm... the opposite end. What's even over there? 
mark: Uh...the supply corner, I think?
truth: Huh? 
mark: You know. Where people charge their RC cars and drones. All that nerdy stuff. 
truth: Right...
truth: You spend all your time in the tabletop section, and nobody would guess it from the way you look. 
mark: Yeah, yeah. Whatever.